other_tests.findings: Morphologic examination revealed a predominant population of small-to-medium-size cells consistent with blasts. Flow-cytometry showed blasts positive for CD19, CD10, and terminal deoxynucleotidyl transferase, consistent with a precursor B-cell phenotype.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The complete blood count on Day 5 showed a decline in white blood cells from 8300 to 4300 per mm3, with a small number of circulating lymphoblasts noted.

other_tests.findings: Cerebrospinal fluid did not show evidence of leukemic cells.
